# 4. みんなでみのりトーク！

Shiho: Wow, that's pretty...
Honami: Hehe. Yes, it is.
Honami: This is my first time hearing about planetarium weddings, but it's incredible how they can project the night sky onto the walls and ceiling like this...
Shiho: Yeah, I could look at this all day.
Shiho: Actually, we've been here for a while now. Wanna head out?
Honami: Okay!
Shiho: Whoa, my eyes... It's so bright out here...
Honami: M-My eyes are also still trying to adjust... Why don't we sit on that bench for now?
Honami: Thank you for coming here with me today, Shiho. I had so much fun last time, I just had to come back...
Shiho: It's all good. I managed to buy everything I needed for practice, and I didn't have anything planned afterwards.
Shiho: Plus, it was worth the trip. I didn't realize that you could hold weddings at live houses.
Honami: Hehe. I wasn't expecting to have the option to play actual instruments on stage.
Shiho: Me neither. It's pretty common for bands to come play at a wedding, but...
???: Huh?
???: Wait a second... Honami? Shiho?
Shiho: Huh?
Honami: E-Ena...?!
Ena: I had a feeling it was you two. Did you come together?
Honami: Yes, we did. What brings you here, Ena?
Ena: I came to see the dresses they have on exhibit.
Ena: I was thinking about doing an oil painting of one for my art class. It's hard to capture those ruffles just right.
Ena: Have you two been to the dress area yet? It's just over there, and you can apparently try them on.
Honami: Oh, I got to try one on last time, so I might...
???: Aha! There's the fitting area!
Shiho: Huh? That sounded like...
Shiho: Minori...?!
Minori: So, in the fitting area, you can try on all these different dresses!
Minori: Wait, hang on... You can try on literally all of them?! That's amazing!
Comments: <That red one in frame's gorgeous.> <Oh, the one with the mini skirt's really cute.>
Nene: They even have professionals on site to do your hair and makeup, so you can just come as you are and become a beautiful bride. Plus, I'm sure you'll find a dress you like.
Comments: <Whoa, they've really got everything!> <I'd need at least an hour to choose a dress.>
Minori: Hehe. This fitting area is the Bridal Fair's main attraction! I hope you all get a chance to try some of these on when you visit!
Minori: But since we're here...
Minori: I'm gonna take this opportunity to try one on!
Comments: <Woohoo!> <I can't wait to see you in a wedding dress, Minori!> <Try the pink dress! Or that white and blue one!>
Minori: Hehe. You'll just have to wait and see♪
Minori: Anyway, I'm gonna go get cha—
Nene: Oh... W-Wait, Hanasato...!
Minori: Huh?
Nene: What do we do about your stream while you're getting changed? You're also getting your hair done, so it's gonna take thirty minutes at the very least...
Minori: O-Oh, that's right...! I thought I'd just get changed in a flash... I didn't think it through at all!
Comments: <Thirty minutes? What do I do until then?> <Things won't be the same without you, Minori.>
Nene: Oh...
Nene: R-Right... A stream with no one talking does sound bad...
Comments: <Oh, does that mean this is gonna be the Nene Show for the next thirty minutes?>
Minori & Nene: Huh?
Comments: <Hey, good idea!> <I wanna hear more about you, Nene!>
Nene: M-Me...?!
Minori: Slow down, you guys! Nene isn't a streamer, so asking her to take over all of a sudden is too much...
Comments: <Aww!> <All she'd have to do is talk like she would normally.> <Still, we shouldn't force her.>
Nene: Uhh...
Nene: I-If it's just for a little bit, then...
Minori: What?!
Nene: I mean, I'm trying to become a professional actress, so I do sorta need to be able to improvise if there are people who want me to...
Minori: B-But are you sure...?! You don't look so good right now...!!!
Comments: <So, the Nene Show's happening?!> <Can you talk about PXL?> <Awesome!>
Comments: <She's gonna take over?> <What are you gonna talk about?>
Minori: S-So many comments are coming in...!
Nene: Th-They want me to talk that much...?
Nene: I-If that's the case, Hanasato, I'll take over for now...! Feel free to go get changed...!
Minori: O-Okay...
Minori: (I-Is she really gonna be okay...? She looked like she was preparing to go into battle just now...)
Nene: Alright, what should I talk about...?
Comments: <How did you and Minori first meet?> <What's Minori like in real life?> <What's your personal impression of Minori?>
Nene: Oh, interesting... Most of you seem to want me to talk about Hanasato...
Nene: Th-Then, let's get started... We can call this segment... “Ask Me Whatever You Like About Hanasato”...
Nene: O-Or something...
Comments: <Yay! A surprise segment!> <Instant classic!> <This one needs to be archived forever.>
Nene: Hahaha...
Nene: So... I guess I should start by talking about how we first met, huh?
Nene: But that means talking about Hoshi... I'd have to talk about another one of my friends, and how we attend different schools...
Nene: W-Wait... I'm not supposed to talk too much about my private life, am I...?
Minori: (Th-There's smoke coming out of Nene's head!)
Minori: (What do I do...?! Everyone was looking forward to hearing her talk, but she's totally starting to panic...!)
Minori: (Is it really okay for me to go get changed right now?!)
???: Minori!
Minori: Huh...?
Minori: Shiho? Honami? Ena? You guys were all here?!
Shiho: Yeah, we just happened to run into each other a second ago. Wait...
Shiho: Sorry, were you in the middle of doing a stream? It looked like you were talking towards your phone just now...
Minori: Y-Yeah, the thing is...! I'm having a friend temporarily take over for me, but...
Ena: We really didn't know. Sorry for interrupting.
Honami: We'll move to a different area, so please feel free to continue streaming.
Minori: Th-Thanks, I really appreciate it!
Minori: Let's all talk the next chance we...
Minori: Wait a second... All of us... Talking...
Minori: S-Sorry, but I need to ask you all for a really big favor!
Shiho: Whoa, you scared me.
Honami: How can we help, Hanasato?
Minori: S-So...! If possible...!
Minori: Would you be willing to help my friend answer questions about me during her segment?
Ena: Answer questions about you...?
Shiho: Now I see... So Kusanagi's over there doing what she can.
Minori: Y-Yeah... But...
Minori: It looks like she's really at her limit, so I can't just leave her!
Shiho: Right...
Shiho: Then, okay... I can help as long as I don't have to show my face in front of the camera.
Minori: R-Really?!
Shiho: I mean, we can't really leave Kusanagi to fend for herself like this.
Honami: I don't know how much I'll be able to contribute, but I promise to do my best...
Ena: *Sigh* I figure you two would be able to cover things...
Ena: But I guess we're all in this together.
Minori: Honami! Ena! Thank you both so much...!
Minori: Then, please help her! I'm gonna go get changed as fast as I can!
Honami: Okay, have fun.
Shiho: Let's go help Kusanagi, shall we?
Nene: Alright, so now...!
Nene: Three of Hanasato's friends will be joining me as I keep answering questions about her...!
Shiho, Honami & Ena: Nice to meet you all.
Comments: <Cool!> <An all-star lineup of Minori's friends?!> <I can't believe so many have gathered here!>
Nene: (Their offer sort of took me by surprise...)
Nene: (But I really appreciate the help. Acting is one thing, but being an MC's a whole different story.)
Nene: (Still, how to move this conversation along...?)
Nene: (I've talked to Mochizuki and Hinomori before, but really haven't with Shinonome...)
Honami: Can you tell us what you've been talking about up to this point, Kusanagi?
Nene: Oh, so... I've been answering questions that Hanasato's viewers have about her.
Ena: About her?
Nene: Yes. What my friendship with her has been like, what we've done together...
Shiho: Your friendship, huh...?
Shiho: In my case, we just started out as classmates. We were in the same class together during our first year.
Ena: Oh, really?
Nene: So... What was your first impression of her?
Shiho: My first impression...? Well...
Shiho: Mostly that she kept coming over to talk to me...
Ena: It doesn't sound like you were a fan.
Shiho: It's not like that. Back then, I sort of just preferred to be by myself.
Shiho: But as time went on, we gradually got to know each other better. We started having lunch together, she showed me the ropes of the animal caretaker committee...
Shiho: And we even went to the zoo together to tend to real animals.
Comments: <Oh, she talked the other day about how she went to the zoo with a friend!> <That was you?!>
Nene: Taking care of real animals at a real zoo...? That sounds like a lot of fun.
Nene: So, since we're on the subject, can you tell us more about what you guys did?
Shiho: We mostly just cleaned their pens and fed them.
Shiho: Actually, when Minori tried to feed the shoebill they had there, he ended up completely ignoring her... I know I shouldn't have laughed, but I couldn't help myself then...
Comments: <I can totally see that happening.> <As bad as I feel for her, that's a really cute story.>
Shiho: But they did become closer at the end. Best friends, in her words.
Ena: Hehe. She's best friends with a shoebill?
Ena: But I can sort of picture it. Minori's silly and clumsy, but in such a cute way.
Ena: I got to know her when we went to SpoJoy Park together. When we went rollerblading, she ended up going for a tumble while trying to help this other friend of mine.
Honami: What? W-Was she okay?
Ena: Yeah, she didn't get hurt. If anything, she was more worried about my friend.
Nene: Hehe. That definitely sounds like her. She's always doing her best for the sake of others, but in a slightly funny way...
Honami: Actually, something similar happened just the other day.
Honami: This dog and his owner were preparing to compete in a disc dog competition, but the owner ended up getting injured. To my surprise, Minori volunteered to take his place.
Ena: Huh?! How does that happen?!
Nene: (Thank goodness... I wasn't sure how this was gonna go at first, but we've managed to get a good conversation going.)
Comments: <I'm hearing about so many of these things for the first time!> <It's fun to hear all these stories about Minori.>
Nene: (And I'm really glad that Hanasato's fans seem to be enjoying themselves.)
Nene: (But also...)
Nene: (I had no idea that she was friends with so many different people.)
Nene: (Thirty minutes won't be enough at the rate we're going. We could easily do this for a whole hour.)
Honami: Oh, Kusanagi, I'd like to hear about any stories that you have.
Nene: Huh? A-Any that I have?
Shiho: I wanna hear too. Tell us about what you and Minori have done together.
Nene: O-Okay... I don't know if I'll be able to tell this story right...
Nene: But I got my biggest impression of her when...
